name: All Is Dust

Flying, protection from colored spells, annihilator 6

text: You may sacrifice four Eldrazi Spawn rather than pay Hand of Emrakul's mana cost.\nAnnihilator 1 (Whenever this creature attacks, defending player sacrifices a permanent.)
flavor: "I believed in a beautiful god. But this is the true face of the divine."\n—Ayli, Kamsa cleric

flavor: Your pleas for death shall go unheard.

name: Pathrazer of Ulamog
text: Annihilator 3 (Whenever this creature attacks, defending player sacrifices three permanents.)\nPathrazer of Ulamog can't be blocked except by three or more creatures.

text: Put five 0/1 colorless Eldrazi Spawn creature tokens onto the battlefield. They have "Sacrifice this creature: Add {C} to your mana pool."
flavor: "The brood spread far faster than we could kill it. I fear the worst is yet to come."\n—The War Diaries

name: Lone Missionary

flavor: His mission has become a grim pilgrimage, a tour of the Eldrazi-stricken outposts across Zendikar. But he marches on alone, stubborn as the daily dawn.

name: Luminous Wake
text: Enchant creature\nWhenever enchanted creature attacks or blocks, you gain 4 life.
flavor: "If destiny's champions have arisen to fight the Ancient Ones, then let me, too, do my part."\n—Ravuel of Graypelt

name: Makindi Griffin
text: Flying
flavor: As the hedrons began to coalesce into colossal Eldrazi superstructures, the griffins were forced to seek new territory lest their aeries be crushed between the massive stone monoliths.

name: Mammoth Umbra
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +3/+3 and has vigilance.\nTotem armor (If enchanted creature would be destroyed, instead remove all damage from it and destroy this Aura.)

name: Near-Death Experience
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, if you have exactly 1 life, you win the game.
flavor: Lands ravaged, cities in ruins, so many lives sacrificed, and yet there was no other word for it but victory.

name: Nomads' Assembly
text: Put a 1/1 white Kor Soldier creature token onto the battlefield for each creature you control.\nRebound (If you cast this spell from your hand, exile it as it resolves. At the beginning of your next upkeep, you may cast this card from exile without paying its mana cost.)

name: Oust
text: Put target creature into its owner's library second from the top. Its controller gains 3 life.
flavor: "‘Invincible' is just a word."\n—Gideon Jura

name: Puncturing Light
text: Destroy target attacking or blocking creature with power 3 or less.
flavor: "The vampires knew what was coming. I know it. And they did nothing. They deserve to feel the same agony they've caused all of us."\n—Anitan, Ondu cleric

name: Repel the Darkness
text: Tap up to two target creatures.\nDraw a card.
flavor: A boon to those who cannot see in the dark. A bane to those who live in it.

name: Smite
text: Destroy target blocked creature.
flavor: "The mighty rely solely on their strength. They are shocked when we do the same."\n—Tars Olan, kor world-gift

name: Soul's Attendant
text: Whenever another creature enters the battlefield, you may gain 1 life.
flavor: In truth, her own faith was gone, trodden in Ulamog's wake. She pantomimed the blessing in the hope that it would inspire others to continue to struggle.

name: Soulbound Guardians
text: Defender, flying
flavor: The kor's most righteous dead are given the greatest reward: an eternity tied to the land they so cherish.

name: Stalwart Shield-Bearers

flavor: "The secret entrance should be near."

name: See Beyond

flavor: Ancient lore locked in a mind driven mad is just as safe as when it was locked deep underground.

flavor: Riches must be divided, but real wealth can be shared.

name: Arrogant Bloodlord
text: Whenever Arrogant Bloodlord blocks or becomes blocked by a creature with power 1 or less, destroy Arrogant Bloodlord at end of combat.
flavor: "I would rather take my own head than be thwarted by a presumptuous wretch with a shield and a dream."

name: Bala Ged Scorpion
text: When Bala Ged Scorpion enters the battlefield, you may destroy target creature with power 1 or less.
flavor: Fast and lethal, with a penchant for the weak and infirm.

name: Baneful Omen
text: At the beginning of your end step, you may reveal the top card of your library. If you do, each opponent loses life equal to that card's converted mana cost.
flavor: "Ah, again it does not bode well for you."

name: Bloodrite Invoker
text: {8}: Target player loses 3 life and you gain 3 life.
flavor: "The brood lineages unfolded across the world, each patterned after one of three progenitors, each a study in mindless consumption."\n—The Invokers' Tales

name: Bloodthrone Vampire
text: Sacrifice a creature: Bloodthrone Vampire gets +2/+2 until end of turn.
flavor: Some humans willingly offered up their blood, hoping it would grant the vampire families the strength to stave off the Eldrazi.

name: Cadaver Imp
text: Flying\nWhen Cadaver Imp enters the battlefield, you may return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: The mouth must be pried open before rigor mortis sets in. Otherwise the returning soul can find no ingress.

name: Consume the Meek
text: Destroy each creature with converted mana cost 3 or less. They can't be regenerated.
flavor: "Why does it destroy? It does, and to talk of reasons wastes time and breath."\n—Nirthu, lone missionary

name: Consuming Vapors
text: Target player sacrifices a creature. You gain life equal to that creature's toughness.\nRebound (If you cast this spell from your hand, exile it as it resolves. At the beginning of your next upkeep, you may cast this card from exile without paying its mana cost.)

name: Contaminated Ground
text: Enchant land\nEnchanted land is a Swamp.\nWhenever enchanted land becomes tapped, its controller loses 2 life.
flavor: "The Na Plateau is lost. Do not ask what happened, and never return there."\n—Nirthu, lone missionary

name: Corpsehatch
text: Destroy target nonblack creature. Put two 0/1 colorless Eldrazi Spawn creature tokens onto the battlefield. They have "Sacrifice this creature: Add {C} to your mana pool."

name: Curse of Wizardry
text: As Curse of Wizardry enters the battlefield, choose a color.\nWhenever a player casts a spell of the chosen color, that player loses 1 life.
flavor: "We must all push through the pain to heal our world."\n—Ayli, Kamsa cleric

name: Death Cultist
text: Sacrifice Death Cultist: Target player loses 1 life and you gain 1 life.
flavor: Death inevitably seduces all who study it.

name: Demonic Appetite

name: Nirkana Revenant
text: Whenever you tap a Swamp for mana, add {B} to your mana pool (in addition to the mana the land produces).\n{B}: Nirkana Revenant gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: Hate is an everlasting wellspring from which it is eternally sustained.

name: Null Champion
text:
Level up {3} ({3}: Put a level counter on this. Level up only as a sorcery.)
LEVEL 1-3
4/2
LEVEL 4+
7/3
{B}: Regenerate Null Champion.

name: Pawn of Ulamog
text: Whenever Pawn of Ulamog or another nontoken creature you control dies, you may put a 0/1 colorless Eldrazi Spawn creature token onto the battlefield. It has "Sacrifice this creature: Add {C} to your mana pool."

name: Perish the Thought
text: Target opponent reveals his or her hand. You choose a card from it. That player shuffles that card into his or her library.
flavor: It removed only one idea from her mind: defiance.

name: Pestilence Demon
text: Flying\n{B}: Pestilence Demon deals 1 damage to each creature and each player.
flavor: "I have schemed too long to be supplanted by dead gods. If I cannot have this world, no one can."

name: Repay in Kind
text: Each player's life total becomes the lowest life total among all players.
flavor: Sorin has gathered grudges for centuries, patiently awaiting the day he can exact the perfect vengeance.

name: Shrivel
text: All creatures get -1/-1 until end of turn.
flavor: "Have you ever killed insects nibbling at your crops? I think that's what the Eldrazi believe they're doing to us."\n—Sheyda, Ondu gamekeeper

name: Skeletal Wurm
text: {B}: Regenerate Skeletal Wurm.
flavor: Necromancers are judged by the most powerful undead they've ever created. There are those who have animated just a single being, yet are considered the pinnacle of their dark craft.

name: Suffer the Past
text: Exile X target cards from target player's graveyard. For each card exiled this way, that player loses 1 life and you gain 1 life.
flavor: Ulamog's tentacles, their touch like burning ice, rummaged through his soul and stung his memories one by one.

name: Thought Gorger
text: Trample\nWhen Thought Gorger enters the battlefield, put a +1/+1 counter on it for each card in your hand. If you do, discard your hand.\nWhen Thought Gorger leaves the battlefield, draw a card for each +1/+1 counter on it.

name: Vendetta
text: Destroy target nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated. You lose life equal to that creature's toughness.
flavor: "Consider my debt to your kin paid in full."\n—Idrol, Guul Draz assassin

name: Virulent Swipe
text: Target creature gets +2/+0 and gains deathtouch until end of turn.\nRebound (If you cast this spell from your hand, exile it as it resolves. At the beginning of your next upkeep, you may cast this card from exile without paying its mana cost.)

name: Zof Shade
text: {2}{B}: Zof Shade gets +2/+2 until end of turn.
flavor: It haunts the remnants of the Helix of Zof, leeching strength from the vast Eldrazi ruin.

name: Zulaport Enforcer
text:
Level up {4} ({4}: Put a level counter on this. Level up only as a sorcery.)
LEVEL 1-2
3/3
LEVEL 3+
5/5
Zulaport Enforcer can't be blocked except by black creatures.

name: Akoum Boulderfoot
text: When Akoum Boulderfoot enters the battlefield, it deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "If you're in Akoum and you glimpse a shadow overhead, the worst thing you can do is duck."\n—Chadir the Navigator

name: Battle Rampart
text: Defender\n{T}: Target creature gains haste until end of turn.
flavor: "I will build no sanctuaries. The safety you seek can be won only by the sword."\n—Yannash, outpost builder

name: Battle-Rattle Shaman
text: At the beginning of combat on your turn, you may have target creature get +2/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: The shaman rattles not to inspire a battle fury but to drown out the shrieks of those fleeing the Eldrazi.

name: Brimstone Mage
text:
Level up {3}{R} ({3}{R}: Put a level counter on this. Level up only as a sorcery.)
LEVEL 1-2
2/3
{T}: Brimstone Mage deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
LEVEL 3+
2/4
{T}: Brimstone Mage deals 3 damage to target creature or player.

name: Brood Birthing
text: If you control an Eldrazi Spawn, put three 0/1 colorless Eldrazi Spawn creature tokens onto the battlefield. They have "Sacrifice this creature: Add {C} to your mana pool." Otherwise, put one of those tokens onto the battlefield.

name: Conquering Manticore
text: Flying\nWhen Conquering Manticore enters the battlefield, gain control of target creature an opponent controls until end of turn. Untap that creature. It gains haste until end of turn.
flavor: It speaks no commands but is always obeyed.

name: Devastating Summons
text: As an additional cost to cast Devastating Summons, sacrifice X lands.\nPut two X/X red Elemental creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: Things born in magma are always angry.

name: Disaster Radius
text: As an additional cost to cast Disaster Radius, reveal a creature card from your hand.\nDisaster Radius deals X damage to each creature your opponents control, where X is the revealed card's converted mana cost.

name: Emrakul's Hatcher
text: When Emrakul's Hatcher enters the battlefield, put three 0/1 colorless Eldrazi Spawn creature tokens onto the battlefield. They have "Sacrifice this creature: Add {C} to your mana pool."
flavor: Wordlessly it leads its abhorrent brood.

name: Explosive Revelation
text: Choose target creature or player. Reveal cards from the top of your library until you reveal a nonland card. Explosive Revelation deals damage equal to that card's converted mana cost to that creature or player. Put the nonland card into your hand and the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.

name: Fissure Vent
text: Choose one or both —\n• Destroy target artifact.\n• Destroy target nonbasic land.
flavor: "Something down there has an appetite for what we're standing on. Let's hope it doesn't want seconds."\n—Samila, Murasa Expeditionary House

name: Flame Slash
text: Flame Slash deals 4 damage to target creature.
flavor: After millennia asleep, the Eldrazi had forgotten about Zendikar's fiery temper and dislike of strangers.

name: Forked Bolt
text: Forked Bolt deals 2 damage divided as you choose among one or two target creatures and/or players.
flavor: "Play no favorites. Everybody dies."\n—Sparkmage saying

name: Goblin Arsonist
text: When Goblin Arsonist dies, you may have it deal 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: With great power comes great risk of getting yourself killed.

name: Goblin Tunneler
text: {T}: Target creature with power 2 or less can't be blocked this turn.
flavor: "You never know what's going to be in goblin tunnels. Even in the best case, there will still be goblins."\n—Sachir, Akoum Expeditionary House

name: Grotag Siege-Runner
text: {R}, Sacrifice Grotag Siege-Runner: Destroy target creature with defender. Grotag Siege-Runner deals 2 damage to that creature's controller.
flavor: "I don't think he's bringing in the mail . . . ."\n—Nundari, Sea Gate militia captain

name: Heat Ray
text: Heat Ray deals X damage to target creature.
flavor: "There was clearly a scream. I'm not sure if there was a mouth."\n—Sachir, Akoum Expeditionary House

name: Hellion Eruption
text: Sacrifice all creatures you control, then put that many 4/4 red Hellion creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: Just when you thought you'd be safe, in the middle of an open field with no Eldrazi around for miles.

name: Kargan Dragonlord
text:
Level up {R} ({R}: Put a level counter on this. Level up only as a sorcery.)
LEVEL 4-7
4/4
Flying
LEVEL 8+
8/8
Flying, trample
{R}: Kargan Dragonlord gets +1/+0 until end of turn.

name: Kiln Fiend
text: Whenever you cast an instant or sorcery spell, Kiln Fiend gets +3/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: It traps an explosion within its stony skin.

name: Lagac Lizard
flavor: Tracing their ancestry back to Zendikar's earliest forms of life, lagac lizards have seen the comings and goings of planeswalkers and the Eldrazi, and the rise of the vampire clans, none of which has changed them one bit.

name: Lavafume Invoker
text: {8}: Creatures you control get +3/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: "Then the ancient masters themselves, towers of rapacity, rose and began their calamitous feast."\n—The Invokers' Tales

name: Lord of Shatterskull Pass
text:
Level up {1}{R} ({1}{R}: Put a level counter on this. Level up only as a sorcery.)
LEVEL 1-5
6/6
LEVEL 6+
6/6
Whenever Lord of Shatterskull Pass attacks, it deals 6 damage to each creature defending player controls.

name: Lust for War
text: Enchant creature\nWhenever enchanted creature becomes tapped, Lust for War deals 3 damage to that creature's controller.\nEnchanted creature attacks each turn if able.

name: Magmaw
text: {1}, Sacrifice a nonland permanent: Magmaw deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "The purpose of existence is simple: everything is fuel for the magmaw."\n—Jaji, magmaw worshipper

name: Ogre Sentry
text: Defender
flavor: "You have to appreciate the genius of it. Why bother building defenses when you can just fill the pass with angry ogres?"\n—Javad Nasrin, Ondu relic hunter

name: Rage Nimbus
text: Defender, flying\n{1}{R}: Target creature attacks this turn if able.
flavor: The settlement knew there was something strange about the cloud when the old priest Mandli suddenly grabbed an axe and ran screaming into the hills.

name: Raid Bombardment
text: Whenever a creature you control with power 2 or less attacks, Raid Bombardment deals 1 damage to defending player.
flavor: Goblins in the first wave of a fire raid always bemoan the aim of everyone else.

name: Rapacious One
text: Trample\nWhenever Rapacious One deals combat damage to a player, put that many 0/1 colorless Eldrazi Spawn creature tokens onto the battlefield. They have "Sacrifice this creature: Add {C} to your mana pool."

name: Soulsurge Elemental
text: First strike\nSoulsurge Elemental's power is equal to the number of creatures you control.
flavor: It draws its strength from those around it, but the pleasure of destruction is all its own.

name: Spawning Breath
text: Spawning Breath deals 1 damage to target creature or player. Put a 0/1 colorless Eldrazi Spawn creature token onto the battlefield. It has "Sacrifice this creature: Add {C} to your mana pool."
flavor: Death by death, Kozilek's lineage spread.

name: Splinter Twin
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature has "{T}: Put a token that's a copy of this creature onto the battlefield. That token has haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step."
flavor: "I know just the person for that job."

name: Staggershock
text: Staggershock deals 2 damage to target creature or player.\nRebound (If you cast this spell from your hand, exile it as it resolves. At the beginning of your next upkeep, you may cast this card from exile without paying its mana cost.)

name: Surreal Memoir
text: Return an instant card at random from your graveyard to your hand.\nRebound (If you cast this spell from your hand, exile it as it resolves. At the beginning of your next upkeep, you may cast this card from exile without paying its mana cost.)

name: Traitorous Instinct
text: Gain control of target creature until end of turn. Untap that creature. Until end of turn, it gets +2/+0 and gains haste.
flavor: The horror lurched about like a puppet from a madman's nightmare, squeezing the life from its own kind.

name: Tuktuk the Explorer
text: Haste\nWhen Tuktuk the Explorer dies, put a legendary 5/5 colorless Goblin Golem artifact creature token named Tuktuk the Returned onto the battlefield.
flavor: Remade by Eldrazi magic, Tuktuk inspired an entire clan of misguided goblins.

name: Valakut Fireboar
text: Whenever Valakut Fireboar attacks, switch its power and toughness until end of turn.
flavor: "Just move very slowly, and for the love of Ula, do not get it mad."\n—Chadir the Navigator

name: Vent Sentinel
text: Defender\n{1}{R}, {T}: Vent Sentinel deals damage to target player equal to the number of creatures with defender you control.
flavor: "Zendikar fortifies itself against the Great Threat, making sentries of sky, sea, and stone."\n—The War Diaries

name: World at War
text: After the first postcombat main phase this turn, there's an additional combat phase followed by an additional main phase. At the beginning of that combat, untap all creatures that attacked this turn.\nRebound (If you cast this spell from your hand, exile it as it resolves. At the beginning of your next upkeep, you may cast this card from exile without paying its mana cost.)

name: Wrap in Flames
text: Wrap in Flames deals 1 damage to each of up to three target creatures. Those creatures can't block this turn.
flavor: "Our pyromancer's flames may not have killed them, but they bought us the time we needed."\n—The War Diaries

name: Ancient Stirrings
text: Look at the top five cards of your library. You may reveal a colorless card from among them and put it into your hand. Then put the rest on the bottom of your library in any order. (Cards with no colored mana in their mana costs are colorless. Lands are also colorless.)

name: Aura Gnarlid
text: Creatures with power less than Aura Gnarlid's power can't block it.\nAura Gnarlid gets +1/+1 for each Aura on the battlefield.
flavor: Kill a gnarlid with your first blow, or it'll cheerfully show you how it's done.

name: Awakening Zone
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, you may put a 0/1 colorless Eldrazi Spawn creature token onto the battlefield. It has "Sacrifice this creature: Add {C} to your mana pool."
flavor: The ground erupted in time with the hedron's thrum, a dirge of the last days.

name: Bear Umbra
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/+2 and has "Whenever this creature attacks, untap all lands you control."\nTotem armor (If enchanted creature would be destroyed, instead remove all damage from it and destroy this Aura.)

text:
Level up {2}{G} ({2}{G}: Put a level counter on this. Level up only as a sorcery.)

name: Boar Umbra
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +3/+3.\nTotem armor (If enchanted creature would be destroyed, instead remove all damage from it and destroy this Aura.)
flavor: "From in here, everything looks like dinner."

name: Bramblesnap
text: Trample\nTap an untapped creature you control: Bramblesnap gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: A bramblesnap is formed by grafting together thirteen different plants that already hunger for meat.

name: Broodwarden
text: Eldrazi Spawn creatures you control get +2/+1.
flavor: "The least of gods shall tower over the mightiest of mortals, and death shall reign over all."\n—Crypt of Agadeem inscription

name: Daggerback Basilisk
text: Deathtouch
flavor: "Petrifying gaze, deadly fangs, knifelike dorsal spines, venomous saliva . . . Am I missing anything? . . . Toxic bones? Seriously?"\n—Samila, Murasa Expeditionary House

name: Gelatinous Genesis
text: Put X X/X green Ooze creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: Even as the world was left cracked and gory by the marauding Eldrazi, new life began to drip from its wounds.

name: Gigantomancer
text: {1}: Target creature you control has base power and toughness 7/7 until end of turn.
flavor: "All life is driven by an indomitable will to survive. I simply turn that into something more . . . tangible."

name: Gravity Well
text: Whenever a creature with flying attacks, it loses flying until end of turn.
flavor: Storms spread throughout Oran-Rief, ripping the skies with wind and rain. Airborne creatures sought shelter where they could.

name: Growth Spasm
text: Search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle your library. Put a 0/1 colorless Eldrazi Spawn creature token onto the battlefield. It has "Sacrifice this creature: Add {C} to your mana pool."

name: Haze Frog
text: Flash (You may cast this spell any time you could cast an instant.)\nWhen Haze Frog enters the battlefield, prevent all combat damage that other creatures would deal this turn.
flavor: Its breath leaves its prey too drowsy to struggle.

name: Irresistible Prey
text: Target creature must be blocked this turn if able.\nDraw a card.
flavor: The baloth's instincts boiled, its muscles pulled taut, and its razor-spines bristled, as it turned to face—a runt meepling.

name: Jaddi Lifestrider
text: When Jaddi Lifestrider enters the battlefield, you may tap any number of untapped creatures you control. You gain 2 life for each creature tapped this way.
flavor: Nature's arms encircle all who are willing to draw close.

name: Joraga Treespeaker
text:
Level up {1}{G} ({1}{G}: Put a level counter on this. Level up only as a sorcery.)
LEVEL 1-4
1/2
{T}: Add {G}{G} to your mana pool.
LEVEL 5+
1/4
Elves you control have "{T}: Add {G}{G} to your mana pool."

name: Kazandu Tuskcaller
text:
Level up {1}{G} ({1}{G}: Put a level counter on this. Level up only as a sorcery.)
LEVEL 2-5
1/1
{T}: Put a 3/3 green Elephant creature token onto the battlefield.
LEVEL 6+
1/1
{T}: Put two 3/3 green Elephant creature tokens onto the battlefield.

name: Khalni Hydra
text: Khalni Hydra costs {G} less to cast for each green creature you control.\nTrample
flavor: "In ages past, bargains were struck and promises were made. Now we must collect on our debt. Begin the hymns."\n—Moruul, Khalni druid

name: Kozilek's Predator
text: When Kozilek's Predator enters the battlefield, put two 0/1 colorless Eldrazi Spawn creature tokens onto the battlefield. They have "Sacrifice this creature: Add {C} to your mana pool."
flavor: It's difficult to outwit something that doesn't speak, strategize, or even think.

name: Leaf Arrow
text: Leaf Arrow deals 3 damage to target creature with flying.
flavor: "Those who think the trees shall remain bystanders throughout this conflict shall be sorely mistaken."\n—Sutina, Speaker of the Tajuru

name: Living Destiny
text: As an additional cost to cast Living Destiny, reveal a creature card from your hand.\nYou gain life equal to the revealed card's converted mana cost.
flavor: "That our enemies are great only brings us greater hope."

name: Might of the Masses
text: Target creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn for each creature you control.
flavor: The Joraga elves never need ask a troll to leave their territory. They merely grant it their combined strength, and it can't resist embarking on a merry rampage.

name: Momentous Fall
text: As an additional cost to cast Momentous Fall, sacrifice a creature.\nYou draw cards equal to the sacrificed creature's power, then you gain life equal to its toughness.
flavor: It wasn't long until the elves had developed a use for every part of the Eldrazi.

name: Mul Daya Channelers
text: Play with the top card of your library revealed.\nAs long as the top card of your library is a creature card, Mul Daya Channelers gets +3/+3.\nAs long as the top card of your library is a land card, Mul Daya Channelers has "{T}: Add two mana of any one color to your mana pool."

name: Naturalize
text: Destroy target artifact or enchantment.
flavor: "The scholars wept when we destroyed the hedron. I had no such pity. What would this world be like had we done so sooner?"\n—The War Diaries

name: Nema Siltlurker
flavor: In one gargantuan bite, it will swallow not only you but also the riverbank you were standing on.

name: Nest Invader
text: When Nest Invader enters the battlefield, put a 0/1 colorless Eldrazi Spawn creature token onto the battlefield. It has "Sacrifice this creature: Add {C} to your mana pool."
flavor: It nurtures its masters' glorious future.

name: Ondu Giant
text: When Ondu Giant enters the battlefield, you may search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle your library.
flavor: Some druids nurture gardens. Others nurture continents.

name: Overgrown Battlement
text: Defender\n{T}: Add {G} to your mana pool for each creature with defender you control.
flavor: "Our enemy is nothing less than the end of all life. We shall not want for allies."\n—The War Diaries

name: Pelakka Wurm
text: Trample\nWhen Pelakka Wurm enters the battlefield, you gain 7 life.\nWhen Pelakka Wurm dies, draw a card.
flavor: It eats what it wants to eat—which is anything that moves.

name: Prey's Vengeance
text: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn.\nRebound (If you cast this spell from your hand, exile it as it resolves. At the beginning of your next upkeep, you may cast this card from exile without paying its mana cost.)

name: Realms Uncharted
text: Search your library for up to four land cards with different names and reveal them. An opponent chooses two of those cards. Put the chosen cards into your graveyard and the rest into your hand. Then shuffle your library.

name: Snake Umbra
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +1/+1 and has "Whenever this creature deals damage to an opponent, you may draw a card."\nTotem armor (If enchanted creature would be destroyed, instead remove all damage from it and destroy this Aura.)

name: Spider Umbra
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +1/+1 and has reach. (It can block creatures with flying.)\nTotem armor (If enchanted creature would be destroyed, instead remove all damage from it and destroy this Aura.)

name: Sporecap Spider
text: Reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)
flavor: "They don't move much, but then again, if you get caught in its web, it has all the time in the world to get to you."\n—Saidah, Joraga hunter

name: Stomper Cub
text: Trample
flavor: "This one is only a yearling, but it would be wise to move away before we provide it with excellent hunting practice."\n—Samila, Murasa Expeditionary House

name: Tajuru Preserver
text: Spells and abilities your opponents control can't cause you to sacrifice permanents.
flavor: "No more blood shall be spilled to satisfy another's deluded lust for power."

name: Vengevine
text: Haste\nWhenever you cast a spell, if it's the second creature spell you cast this turn, you may return Vengevine from your graveyard to the battlefield.
flavor: Leave but a shred of root and it will return, bursting with vigor.

name: Wildheart Invoker
text: {8}: Target creature gets +5/+5 and gains trample until end of turn.
flavor: "Life as we know it dangles on the brink of extinction. We must show the strength they would steal from us."\n—The Invokers' Tales

name: Sarkhan the Mad
text: 0: Reveal the top card of your library and put it into your hand. Sarkhan the Mad deals damage to himself equal to that card's converted mana cost.\n−2: Target creature's controller sacrifices it, then that player puts a 5/5 red Dragon creature token with flying onto the battlefield.\n−4: Each Dragon creature you control deals damage equal to its power to target player.

name: Angelheart Vial
text: Whenever you're dealt damage, you may put that many charge counters on Angelheart Vial.\n{2}, {T}, Remove four charge counters from Angelheart Vial: You gain 2 life and draw a card.
flavor: It holds a whisper from Iona: "Persevere."

name: Dreamstone Hedron
text: {T}: Add {C}{C}{C} to your mana pool.\n{3}, {T}, Sacrifice Dreamstone Hedron: Draw three cards.
flavor: Only the Eldrazi mind thinks in the warped paths required to open the hedrons and tap the power within.

name: Enatu Golem
text: When Enatu Golem dies, you gain 4 life.
flavor: Golems conjured from the debris of Enatu Temple provided a sturdy but expendable first line of defense against the Eldrazi.

name: Hedron Matrix
text: Equipped creature gets +X/+X, where X is its converted mana cost.\nEquip {4}
flavor: The hedrons awoke along with the Eldrazi, forming superstructures that radiated overwhelming magic.

name: Keening Stone
text: {5}, {T}: Target player puts the top X cards of his or her library into his or her graveyard, where X is the number of cards in that player's graveyard.
flavor: As it spins, dead voices shriek in an ever-increasing cacophony, rending the mind asunder.

name: Ogre's Cleaver
text: Equipped creature gets +5/+0.\nEquip {5}
flavor: She adopted the weapon of the slave-lord Kazuul, and with it, all his cruelty.

name: Pennon Blade
text: Equipped creature gets +1/+1 for each creature you control.\nEquip {4}
flavor: Draped with the pennon of a fallen outpost, the sword came to symbolize the peoples of Zendikar becoming one.

name: Prophetic Prism
text: When Prophetic Prism enters the battlefield, draw a card.\n{1}, {T}: Add one mana of any color to your mana pool.
flavor: "The explorer who found it got a bad deal when he sold it. He merely got rich."

name: Reinforced Bulwark
text: Defender\n{T}: Prevent the next 1 damage that would be dealt to you this turn.
flavor: Built of wood and iron. Held together by hope and prayer.

name: Runed Servitor
text: When Runed Servitor dies, each player draws a card.
flavor: Scholars had puzzled for centuries over the ruins at Tal Terig. Its secrets had always lived within one rune-carved head.

name: Sphinx-Bone Wand
text: Whenever you cast an instant or sorcery spell, you may put a charge counter on Sphinx-Bone Wand. If you do, Sphinx-Bone Wand deals damage equal to the number of charge counters on it to target creature or player.
flavor: Its host's final curse lies captured within.

name: Warmonger's Chariot
text: Equipped creature gets +2/+2.\nAs long as equipped creature has defender, it can attack as though it didn't have defender.\nEquip {3} ({3}: Attach to target creature you control. Equip only as a sorcery.)
flavor: The best defense is a good offense.

name: Eldrazi Temple
text: {T}: Add {C} to your mana pool.\n{T}: Add {C}{C} to your mana pool. Spend this mana only to cast colorless Eldrazi spells or activate abilities of colorless Eldrazi.
flavor: Each temple is a door to a horrible future.

name: Evolving Wilds
text: {T}, Sacrifice Evolving Wilds: Search your library for a basic land card and put it onto the battlefield tapped. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Every world is an organism, able to grow new lands. Some just do it faster than others.
